<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Sim_VacationsBG" s="254315">
  <T n="category">10175<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_SimLife--></T>
  <T n="name">0x1F43F1AE<!--String: "Vacations"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Vacations_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5d756717405c2567</T>
      <T n="text">0x2B00A312<!--String: "Sims wanting to take a vacation and travel to a new locale may do so by clicking on the “Take a Vacation” interaction in the Travel section of their Phone, or from a computer. Up to eight Sims can go on Vacation together at a time. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Vacations_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5d756717405c2564</T>
      <T n="text">0x7A45D08A<!--String: "When going on Vacation, a Sim can choose to Vacation in any Residential World that contains a Rental venue lot. With certain expansions, they may also visit a Destination World instead. These are worlds that Sims may only vacation in and may not use as a residence.\n\nAfter selecting a world, choose a Rental lot for the selected Sim(s) to live in throughout the duration of the vacation. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Vacations_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5d756717405c2565</T>
      <T n="text">0x10A0A021<!--String: "When Sims reserve their home away from home, the active Household must pay daily rent up front. Rent is dependent on the Lot Value for the selected Lot. There is a drop down that allows players to choose how many days they would like their vacationers to rent the lot. A total tally of cost is displayed on the bottom right hand side of this menu. Helpful Tip: Once in game, Sims may use the Travel section of their Phone to choose to extend their vacation or end it early. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Vacations_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5d756717405c2562</T>
      <T n="text">0xD0E95839<!--String: "While on vacation, Build Mode is locked. Sims on vacation in Residential Worlds may purchase necessities on their phone in the Household section with the “Order Supplies Now…” interaction. Destination Worlds have unique locations to purchase supplies for that world."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Vacations_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5d756717405c2563</T>
      <T n="text">0xA36D0150<!--String: "Adding a new Rental lot to any world is easy! Travel to any lot that does not have a Household already occupying it. Once in Build Mode, on the upper left hand side of the screen, select the Venue Info icon. From there, the venue can be changed to “Rental” from the Lot Type drop down. This lot is now a Rental Lot. While in Build Mode, be sure to place any objects you’d like to have available to future vacationers. "--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <T n="ui_sort_order">223</T>
</I>